    <stitle>NEWAY AD-123/246 DRIVE AXLE AIR SUSPENSIONS - REPLACE - SUSPENSION AIR SPRINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SUSPENSION AIR SPRINGS</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Be sure to use proper air spring replacement. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301011">Figure 11</hotlnk>
                    for air spring identification.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f0301011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0301011" filename="../figg03/G0301011.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Air Spring Identification</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prior to removing air spring, vehicle must be unloaded. Support vehicle frame with adequate
                jack stands at approximate air spring height.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Jack stands must be of sufficient strength to support the vehicle.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Exhaust air from suspension system by:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Height control valve - disconnect link at lower connection, then rotate control arm to
                    exhaust (approximately 45&#176; down) position. Drain all air from reservoir.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Disconnect air supply line from air spring.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect and remove old air spring assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new air spring assembly and properly tighten fasteners to 30 to 35 ft-lbs. (41 to 47
                N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect air supply line and link connections.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove jack stands.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Build suspension air supply system pressure in excess of 65 psi. Check for leaks.</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>100 psi is maximum allowable operating air system pressure.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If ride adjustment is necessary, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s03010_13.xml" xrefid="hl0301002">ADJUSTMENT</hotlnk>
                for proper procedure.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
